Healthified Chicken & Mash Bowl
http://www.theskinnyfork.com/blog/chicken-mash-bowl
Servings: 4

Brown Gravy:
1 1/2 c chicken broth
3 Tbsp White Whole Wheat Flour
1/2 tsp Onion Powder
1/4 c Light Butter

Mashed potatoes
2 c Mixed Vegetables, Steamed
Leftover chicken

Place the ingredients for the gravy into a medium sauce pan and whisk over
medium-high heat until the mixture begins to bubble and thicken.  Remove from
the heat and allow to cool slightly.

Place about 3/4 c of the potatoes in the bottom of each bowl and top with
about 1/4 c of the mixed vegetables.

Add the chicken over the top of the vegetables.  Top with gravy and enjoy!
